'''分居'''（{{lang-en|Marital separation}}）是指[[伴侶|伴侶]]或[[親屬|親屬]]停止[[同居|同居]]生活。主要原因有三：第一為正處理[[離婚|離婚]]手續<ref>{{Cite web|title=離婚手續|url=https://smithfield-divorce.com/離婚手續/|accessdate=2021-04-30|work=史密夫事務所|language=zh-hant|archive-date=2021-05-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210505184945/https://smithfield-divorce.com/%e9%9b%a2%e5%a9%9a%e6%89%8b%e7%ba%8c/|dead-url=no}}</ref>；二為[[婚姻|婚姻]]關係增加前景；第三則為增進婚姻關係<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.psychologytoday.com/blog/contemplating-divorce/201004/can-marital-separation-make-your-marriage-better|title=Can a Marital Separation Make Your Marriage Better?|author=Gadoua, Susan Pease|publisher=Psychology Today|date=25 April 2010}}</ref>。有專家指出6個月的分居是最佳的時間長度，因為這段時間足夠建立第二個住家和透視婚姻前景，但不足夠作為永久分開<ref>{{cite web|url=http://online.wsj.com/news/articles/SB10001424053111904140604576496240815891366|title=To Save a Marriage, Split Up?|author=Bernstein, Elizabeth|date=9 August 2011|publisher=Wall Street Journal|accessdate=2015-04-17|archive-date=2014-10-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141003234900/http://online.wsj.com/news/articles/SB10001424053111904140604576496240815891366|dead-url=no}}</ref>。分居可以非正式進行，但亦可以透過[[分居協議|分居協議]]以開展[[合法分居|合法分居]]。在華語地區而言，分居一詞主要指單方面申請離婚手續後的一段時間，而在美國多數州份如[[維珍尼亞州|維珍尼亞州]]亦然。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://leg1.state.va.us/cgi-bin/legp504.exe?000+cod+20-91|title=§ 20-91. Grounds for divorce from bond of matrimony; contents of decree.|publisher=Code of Virginia|accessdate=2015-04-17|archive-date=2014-09-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140908050557/http://leg1.state.va.us/cgi-bin/legp504.exe?000+cod+20-91|dead-url=no}}</ref>

